Actions in the elastic IP:

1.View details
--------------------------------
\_Show all details of the Elastic  IP
Such as : 
* Public IP
* Allocation ID
* Associated instance / ENI
* Reverse DNS
* Transfer status
* Tags

2.Release Elastic IP address 
--------------------------------
This deletes the Elastic IP from your AWS account 

3.Associate Elastic IP 
---------------------------------
This is used to attach  the Elastic IP to : 
* an EC2 instance
* or a Network Interface (ENI)
* or a NAT Gateway
This is the step where you actually start using the Elastic IP.

4.Disassociate Elastic IP address
-----------------------------------
Remove the Elastic IP from the Ec2 /ENI 
Ec2 will :
* Lose public connectivity immediately
* Stop responding to SSH/RDP if no other public IP exists

5.Update revers DNS 
This is used only if : 
*YOu run a mail server 
AWS lets you set a reverse DNS record (like 123.1.2.3 â†’ mail.example.com).
Normal users never use this.

6.Enabel Tranfer 
-------------------------------------
Allows you to transfer this Elastic IP to another AWS account 

7.Disabel transfer
-------------------------------------
Stops transfer pemissoin if previously enabeled

8.Accept transfer 
--------------------------------------
This appears if another AWS account is transferring an Elastic IP to you 
YOu must accept it to complete transfer 

Summary 
| Action                      | Meaning                                 |
| --------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| **View details**            | See all info about the Elastic IP       |
| **Release Elastic IP**      | Delete/remove it from AWS account       |
| **Associate Elastic IP**    | Attach the IP to an EC2/NAT/ENI         |
| **Disassociate Elastic IP** | Remove the IP from the instance         |
| **Update reverse DNS**      | Configure PTR DNS (mail servers)        |
| **Enable transfers**        | Allow sending IP to another AWS account |
| **Disable transfers**       | Stop transfer option                    |
| **Accept transfers**        | Accept an incoming IP transfer          |
